life right now 🫶🏾

Day 30 of #whole30, I made it 🤩 Over this program I’ve had, lots of walks, @pure_barre classes, gallons of water, one major melt down, cooked with and for friends and family, and more potatoes than I’ve ever eaten in my entire life 😅

Non scale gains: 
- 🚫 stomach pain after eating 
- 🚫 heart burn
- 🚫 sugar spikes or cravings, or mood swings 
- SO much energy
- Better overall mood
- In Jan 2023 I spent less than half of my typical food budget as compared to December 2022 💸
- Abs. I mean. 🙌🏾 💅 

My word for 2023 is patience, and this program challenged every bit of it 😅 I was frustrated that I didn’t see gains right away, I made the mistake of stepping on the scale (this isn’t a weight loss diet!). But after the ups and downs of weeks 1 & 2, I finally felt the gains, internally, externally, and in my wallet 🙌🏾

It doesn’t end here, I’m going to continue to make changes in my everyday life to keep up this energy, who is with me?! 🤩🙋🏾‍♀️

#whole30

This day every year will always be bittersweet for me. It marks the one year anniversary of a show that forever changed my life, but it also is the day when I lost one of the most special people in my life as well. 

Uncle Buncle, you were like a second dad to me. You drove me to and from school and ballet, hosted me for dinner, took me to the movies, ignited my love of camping, and helped me understand black culture through music, writing, and film. 

You were so supportive of me, my parents, and my siblings going on the show, and were so excited to hear all about it when we got back. You wanted to make a big pot of chili premiere day so that we could all eat and watch together- I wish you could have watched it with us. 

You are so missed. You had the kindest soul and the biggest heart. I feel as though what I am saying isn’t even close to fully encapsulating the person you were. There will never be a day that goes by that I won’t miss you. I love you so much. 

🤎,

I have done weaves, relaxers, curly perms, braids, tape ins, frontals, Brazilian blow outs. You name it, I have probably tried it 😅 

But this year, I really wanted to focus on hair health and learning to love what I have naturally. And I’m over halfway through the year and I’ve stuck to the program 🙌🏾

I still get a wash and press every 2-3 weeks, but other than that, I’ve stayed fairly natural and have seen results. Trims and deep conditioning treatments have been vital as well. 

Check out my link in bio and stories for more tips and tricks on my hair care routine! 💇🏾‍♀️🧖🏾‍♀️🤍
